## When Starting a New Phase

1. Read the phase section in the build guide
2. Read `.cursor/rules/recaller-project.mdc` for architecture context
3. Check this file for what's already complete
4. Update this file when the phase is done

## When Completing a Phase (MANDATORY)

1. Run a security audit — scan all staged files for API keys, secrets, tokens. Never commit `.env.local`.
2. Create a detailed conventional commit (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`) with body listing what was built.
3. Push to GitHub: `git push origin main`
4. Verify push succeeded and no secrets leaked.
5. Update this file to mark the phase as completed.
